                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/4787½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        French Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Saint-Quentin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-16">July 16,
                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: The President has asked me to request that
                    Your Excellency be good enough to inform Marshal Pétain that his message of July
                    4 regarding the naval action at Oran, which you handed personally to the
                    President, has been read with interest.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
